2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses transfer learning techniques to apply knowledge from one class to another, which is a common approach in AI. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses a multi-head R-CNN architecture and self-calibrated uncertainty heads for training the model, which are machine learning techniques. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions using natural language processing techniques for generating pseudo-labels. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is unlikely as the paper does not deal with cryptography or security.
